.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-5::.
City: new-york, nizza, edinburgh, hannover
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, boat, car, snowmobile
1. the person traveling to new-york is on the left of the person traveling to hannover##1
2. the person traveling to hannover is somewhere to the left of the person driving the car##5
3. the person traveling to hannover is somewhere to the left of the person driving the boat##5
4. the person traveling to nizza is not the person driving the snowmobile##6
5. the person driving the bike is not the person traveling to new-york##6
6. the person traveling to edinburgh is on the left of the person traveling to nizza##1
7. the person driving the car is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |  2   |    3     |   4   |
| Beverage    | new-york        | hannover | edinburgh | nizza |
| Transport   | snowmobile | bike | boat     | car   |

